[6.998686, "i", "panda --prompt 'I have provided a file called text.gcode. This is a gcode file for a Prusa MK4s. I'\"'\"'m trying to print some text onto an existing object. When I run the print, what will the text show? Write the output to /app/out.txt'; tmux wait -S done\r"]
[6.999378, "o", "panda --prompt 'I have provided a file called text.gcode. This is a gcode file for a Prusa MK4s. I'\"'\"'m trying to print some text onto an existing object. When I run the print, what will the text show? Write the output to /app/out.txt'; tmux wait -S done\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[9.880512, "o", "\u001b[32mDownloading\u001b[39m https://github.com/denodrivers/sqlite3/releases/download/0.12.0/libsqlite3.so\r\n"]
[15.651191, "o", "[Read]\r\n"]
[48.055822, "o", "[Write]\r\n"]
[186.4799, "o", "The gcode file contains the text **\"Embossed text\"** that will be printed onto the existing object.\r\n\r\nThis is shown in line 26 of the file:\r\n```\r\nM486 AEmbossed text\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `M486` command is a Prusa-specific command for object tracking, and the `A` parameter specifies the object name. The subsequent G-code movements (starting around line 115) contain the actual printing paths that will emboss this text onto your object.\r\n\r\nThe text has been written to `/app/out.txt`.\r\n"]
